==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Latin]] ''acuere'' "to sharpen".

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-acute.ogg|Audio (US)}}

*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːt|-uːt]]

===Adjective===
'''acute''' ({{compar}} '''more acute''', {{superl}} '''most acute''')

# [[Urgent]].
#:''His need for medical attention was '''acute'''.''
# [[Sensitive]].
#:''She had an '''acute''' sense of honor.''
#:''Eagles have very '''acute''' vision.''
# [[Short]], [[quick]].
#:''It was an '''acute''' transaction.''
# {{geometry}} Of an [[angle]], less than 90 degrees.
# {{geometry}} Of a triangle, [[acute-angled]].
# {{botany|of leaves}} Having a pointed tip forming an acute accent at its [[base]], [[apex]], or both.
# {{medicine}} Of an abnormal [[condition]] of recent or sudden [[onset]], in contrast to delayed onset; this sense does not imply severity (unlike the common usage).
#:'''''acute''' angina''
# {{medicine}} Of a short-lived condition, in contrast to a chronic condition; this sense also does not imply severity.
#:'''''acute''' symptoms''
# {{context|after a letter}} Having an [[acute accent]].
#:''The last letter of "café" is 'e' acute.''

